      "content": "hey, quick question. i've been noticing some weird stuff with my smart lights and the thermostat lately. like, they seem to react to how i'm feeling even when i don't touch them. if i'm stressed the lights go dim or something. do you think it's actually possible for companies like google or amazon to use affective computing to monitor people through their home devices??",
